OL,6,FHe said: "Words that have been used
OL,7,Fabout killing were like 'flat
OL,8,Fpacking', 'flat packing them'", adding
OL,9,Fthat the words are "quite normal in
OL,10,Fthe military world."
OL,12,FCounsel to the inquiry Oliver Glasgow
OL,13,FKC asked the witness if he had any
OL,14,Fconcerns for his own personal
OL,15,Fwellbeing after making allegations
OL,16,Fagainst the unit. He replied: "I did
OL,17,Fthen and I still do now."
OL,19,FWhen asked if he was concerned with
OL,20,Fbeing "branded as a traitor", N1799
OL,21,Fanswered "yes".
